<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style>
      h2, img, p { margin: 0; } td { padding-top: 0 !important; } p {
      margin-bottom: 10px; }
    </mj-style>
    <!-- <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto+Serif" /> -->
    <mj-font
      name="Roboto+Serif"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?faily=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap"
    />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff" padding-bottom="0px">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image
          padding="10px 12px"
          css-class="light_img"
          width="150px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/logo.png"
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
          alt=""
        />
        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="10px 0px"
        />
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 2px 6px 2px"
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin-top: 2px">
            It’s Independence Day weekend, and we’re marking the occasion with a
            special edition of Presidential Summary. Today, we’re stepping away
            from the usual headlines to look back at how America has celebrated
            July 4th over the decades.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin-top: 2px">
            Enjoy and have a great holiday!
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <!-- <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="0px 0px"
        /> -->
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Header -->
    <mj-spacer height="10px" />
    <!-- July 4th in pictures -->
    <mj-section
      css-class="mj_fsection"
      background-color="#ffffff"
      css-class="mj_fsection"
    >
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text
          padding="2px 12px 0px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="white"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              padding-top: 14px;
              padding-bottom: 8px;
              color: #4d3060;
              text-align: left;
              border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;

              font-size: 26px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
            "
          >
            July 4th in pictures
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- 1 -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff" padding-bottom="6px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            2025 - One Big Beautiful Bill
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/picture-summary/trump-signs-bill-white-house-ceremony.jpg"
          alt="President Donald Trump holds up a signed bill during a celebratory White House ceremony, surrounded by members of Congress."
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
        />

        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i> Credits: Evan Vucci/AP</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            This year’s July 4th comes with major domestic and international
            shifts. At a White House Independence Day ceremony, President Trump
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-5-jul-25-j4ip-h1-1-signed?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >signed</a
            >
            his signature package of tax breaks and spending cuts. Meanwhile,
            the US military is now patrolling nearly one-third of the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-5-jul-25-j4ip-h1-2-us-mexico-border?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >US-Mexico border</a
            >. Soldiers have been given the power to stop and detain people who
            cross illegally, as part of President Trump’s emergency border
            order.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            See more July 4th photos
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-5-jul-25-j4ip-h1-3-here?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >here</a
            >
            (protests and celebrations).
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- 2 -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff" padding-bottom="6px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            2015 - When the Obamas lit up the South Lawn
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/picture-summary/obamas-white-house-4th-july-celebration.jpg"
          alt="Barack and Michelle Obama address a crowd during a Fourth of July celebration on the White House lawn, with stage lights and decorations creating a festive atmosphere."
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
        />

        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>Credits: Reuters </i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            Former President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama
            concluded the nation's 239th Independence Day celebrations with a
            concert by Bruno Mars on the White House South Lawn for the
            military. Meanwhile, people braved tight security along New York
            City's East River for Macy's annual fireworks display. The
            celebrations came amid a surge in terror threats from the Islamic
            State, with counter terrorism police assigned to all city-held
            events.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>
